event.title: Reserve Restaurant Milton
event.summary: Enjoy fine dining and exceptional service on the banks of the River at Milton. Serving contemporary European cuisine with a classical French influence, Chef Kieran Reekie sources the best of Australia's fresh local produce to create dishes that are ingeniously flavoured and exquisitely presented. Combine this with an extensive wine list hand picked by sommelier Stephen Heffernan and discreet service by professional, knowledgeable staff and you can be assured of a first class dining experience.

event.title: Customs House Restaurant
event.summary: Customs House has a licensed restaurant which provides inside dining in heritage surroundings as well as outside dining overlooking the river and the Story Bridge. The relaxed dining ambience is popular with tourists, business clients and local customers. Guests can be assured of excellent food, fantastic river views and friendly professional service. The cuisine is modern Australian with an emphasis on fresh seasonal produce including seafood. The wine list has quality wines at competitive prices.

event.title: Lone Pine Koala Sanctuary
event.summary: Lone Pine Koala Santuary in Brisbane is a wonderful place to visit for all the family if you're interested in Australian fauna. It's one of the few Australian zoos which enables you to feed and touch the animals. The wildlife zoo contains koalas, kangaroos, australian birds, tasmanian devils, wombats, dingoes, reptiles and small farm animals, just to name a few. You can feed the kangaroos any time of the day food which you buy from the local cafe at an extremely cheap price. You can cuddle a koala or a python if you wish and watch live shows about the various animals during the daily program, which are very educational and amusing to watch. If you're visiting Brisbane then it's well worth the effort to visit Lone Pine.
event.address: Jesmond Rd | Fig Tree Pocket, Brisbane, Queensland 4069, Australia
